COURT. Q. How long have you known him? A. He has lodged at my mother's two years and a half;
John Walker
also lodges there, nobody else; they are they only two lodgers we had; my mother was at home when Taylor came in, at a quarter past five o'clock, and that was all -Walker came home about six, and then I went with him to Swallow's.
